President Obama and President Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan had a phone call to discuss various issues in their bilateral relations. They talked about their cooperative efforts in nuclear security, including securing nuclear material from the BN-350 reactor. They also reviewed progress on meeting goals established during their bilateral meeting at the Nuclear Security Summit last year. President Obama thanked President Nazarbayev for his support in fostering security and prosperity in Afghanistan. They also discussed the importance of political modernization alongside economic modernization in Kazakhstan, with the upcoming parliamentary elections in 2012 seen as an opportunity for greater democratization. President Nazarbayev affirmed this goal in his recent inauguration address.